synopsis: After successfully completing their JAPAN Dome concert, the members of B-Project and Tsubasa keep busy pursuing their various jobs. Daikoku Productions president Daikoku Atsushi asks Tsubasa to bring B-Project to a certain location, and...

A joint concert featuring Brave Entertainment units KiLLER KiNG and THRIVE is planned to announce KiLLER KiNG joining B-PROJECT.
Everyone is highly motivated, and practice for the concert seems to be progressing smoothly, but..

With the addition of KiLLER KiNG, B-PROJECT now has 14 members, but all of them are too busy with their respective jobs to meet as a group.
The members decide to throw a welcoming party for KiLLER KiNG, but disaster strikes during the party!?

Kitakore are closely covered for the popular TV show "Fanatical Continent."
Meanwhile, Kitakado and Korekuni receive individual job offers for a drama and commercial respectively. However, they both struggle to perform jobs rather disconnected from their normal image.
Will they be able to finish their jobs and Fanatical Continent coverage without any incident...?

Ashu picks up two tickets to a major artist's concert that Tsubasa happened to drop. Recalling how Tsubasa said those who work hard would be rewarded, Kitakore, THRIVE, and MooNs suddenly begin a battle for a concert date with Tsubasa...

Sekimura suddenly receives a message from his father that forces him to make a difficult decision.
Sekimura agonizes over his choice, but he cannot disobey his father. His decision turns into a major event involving MooNs and B-PROJECT.
Will MooNs and B-PROJECT be able to overcome this difficulty?!

Kitakore and MooNs are asked to appear on a music program produced by a TV station in Hokkaido.
Due to their work schedules, Kitakado flies with four members of MooNs, while Masunaga and Korekuni fly together.
Korekuni uses this opportunity to ask Masunaga how he feels, but...
